description:
Running this full PHP script. When the process ends, the file is not written.
{code:java}
<?php

require __DIR__ . '/../vendor/autoload.php';

$client = new MongoDB\Client(getenv('MONGODB_URI') ?: 'mongodb://127.0.0.1/');
$database = $client->selectDatabase('test');
$database->drop();
$gridfs = $database->selectGridFSBucket();

// Open a stream for writing, similar to fopen with mode 'w'
$stream = $gridfs->openUploadStream('hello.txt');
fwrite($stream, 'Hello world!');
{code}
To get the file written, the stream must be explicitly closed.
{code:java}
fclose($stream);{code}
Note that the stream is correctly closed when this code is wrapped inside a function.

{quote}When used in other supported stages, [{{$sum}}|https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/sum/#mongodb-group-grp.-sum] has one of two syntaxes:
 * [{{$sum}}|https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/sum/#mongodb-group-grp.-sum] has one specified expression as its operand:

{code:java}
{ $sum: <expression> } {code}
 

 * [{{$sum}}|https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/sum/#mongodb-group-grp.-sum] has a list of specified expressions as its operand:
{code:java}
{ $sum: [ <expression1>, <expression2> ... ]  } {code}
 {quote}
Only the 2nd syntax is implemented, because we thought it functionally covered the first with a single expression array.

But in the 1st syntax, the expression can resolve to an array.

Example : [https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/addFields/#using-two--addfields-stages]

See [https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/dateDiff/]
|The time measurement {{unit}} between the {{startDate}} and {{{}endDate{}}}. It is an [expression|https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/#std-label-aggregation-expressions] that resolves to a string:
 * {{year}}
 * {{quarter}}
 * {{week}}
 * {{month}}
 * {{day}}
 * {{hour}}
 * {{minute}}
